{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896022114,"sessionID":"ses_28459852dffeE6AofOxt18H7zK","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba6c9ec001bLbHOqrgAu9636","messageID":"msg_d7ba6c00d001EcfW4aK3BVXPY1","sessionID":"ses_28459852dffeE6AofOxt18H7zK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4596a199c235455f9999eefc672137c7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document summarizes the complete implementation of AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition for the AgentCube project.\n6: \n7: ## Implementation Details\n8: \n9: ### Files Created\n10: \n11: | File | Lines | Description |\n12: |------|-------|-------------|\n13: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go | 732 | Complete Go type definitions for AgentRuntime CRD with all kubebuilder markers |\n14: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go | 48 | Scheme registration and API group configuration |\n15: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go | 12 | Package documentation and kubebuilder markers |\n16: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/deepcopy.go | 1086 | DeepCopy methods for all types |\n17: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go | 1029 | Comprehensive unit tests (32 test cases) |\n18: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md | 168 | Package documentation and usage examples |\n19: | config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml | 1028 | Complete CRD YAML definition with OpenAPI schema |\n20: | config/samples/runtime_v1alpha1_agentruntime.yaml | 99 | Example AgentRuntime YAML |\n21: \n22: **Total**: 4,202 lines of code and documentation\n23: \n24: ### Type Definitions Implemented\n25: \n26: #### Core Types\n27: - `AgentRuntime` - Main CRD type with spec and status\n28: - `AgentRuntimeList` - List type for collection operations\n29: - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - Desired state with PodTemplate, SessionTimeout, MaxSessionDuration\n30: - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - Observed state with Conditions and ObservedGeneration\n31: \n32: #### Sandbox Types (30+ types)\n33: - `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxMetadata`, `SandboxPodSpec`\n34: - `SandboxContainer`, `SandboxContainerPort`, `SandboxEnvVar`, `SandboxEnvVarSource`\n35: - `SandboxProbe`, `SandboxProbeHandler`, `SandboxExecAction`, `SandboxTCPSocketAction`, `SandboxHTTPGetAction`\n36: - `SandboxSecurityContext`, `SandboxCapabilities`, `SandboxSeccompProfile`\n37: - `SandboxAffinity`, `SandboxNodeAffinity`, `SandboxPodAffinity`, `SandboxNodeSelector`\n38: - `SandboxToleration`, `SandboxVolume`, `SandboxVolumeMount`\n39: - `SandboxResources`, `SandboxResourceList`, `SandboxContainerResources`\n40: - And more...\n41: \n42: ### Test Coverage\n43: \n44: All 32 unit tests pass with 100% success rate:\n45: \n46: 1. TestAgentRuntimeTypeMeta\n47: 2. TestAgentRuntimeSchemeGroupVersion\n48: 3. TestResource\n49: 4. TestAgentRuntimeSpecDefaults\n50: 5. TestAgentRuntimeStatusConditions\n51: 6. TestAgentRuntimeList\n52: 7. TestSandboxTemplate\n53: 8. TestSandboxContainer\n54: 9. TestSandboxEnvVarSources (4 subtests)\n55: 10. TestSandboxProbe\n56: 11. TestSandboxAffinity\n57: 12. TestSandboxTolerations\n58: 13. TestSandboxSecurityContext\n59: 14. TestSandboxVolumes\n60: 15. TestJSONSerialization\n61: 16. TestSchemeRegistration\n62: 17. TestAgentRuntimeObjectMeta\n63: 18. TestSandboxContainerPort\n64: 19. TestDurationFields (3 subtests)\n65: 20. TestSandboxResources\n66: 21. TestSandboxVolumeMount\n67: 22. TestSandboxHTTPHeader\n68: 23. TestSandboxExecAction\n69: 24. TestSandboxLabelSelector\n70: 25. TestAgentRuntimeStatus\n71: 26. TestSandboxNodeSelectorTerm\n72: 27. TestSandboxPreferredSchedulingTerm\n73: 28. TestSandboxKeyToPath\n74: 29. TestFullAgentRuntime\n75: 30. TestSchemeContainsTypes\n76: 31. TestAgentRuntimeListTypeMeta\n77: \n78: ### API Contract Compliance\n79: \n80: All requirements from the delta-spec have been implemented:\n81: \n82: ✓ **Type metadata reflects GVR mapping**\n83:   - APIVersion: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n84:   - Kind: `AgentRuntime`\n85: \n86: ✓ **Resource plural matches client-go expectations**\n87:   - Resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n88:   - Short names: `ar`, `agentruntime`\n89: \n90: ✓ **Spec structure with required fields**\n91:   - PodTemplate (required): `*SandboxTemplate`\n92:   - SessionTimeout (optional): `*metav1.Duration` (default: 15m)\n93:   - MaxSessionDuration (optional): `*metav1.Duration` (default: 8h)\n94: \n95: ✓ **Duration fields use metav1 types**\n96:   - Properly serialized as duration strings\n97: \n98: ✓ **Status with conditions support**\n99:   - Conditions: `[]metav1.Condition`\n100:   - ObservedGeneration: `int64`\n101: \n102: ✓ **List type for collection operations**\n103:   - Standard Kubernetes list type with pagination support\n104: \n105: ✓ **Scheme registration for serialization**\n106:   - Full JSON/YAML serialization support\n107:   - DeepCopy methods implemented\n108: \n109: ✓ **CRD subresources support**\n110:   - Status subresource enabled\n111:   - Independent status updates\n112: \n113: ✓ **Default values for spec fields**\n114:   - SessionTimeout: 15m\n115:   - MaxSessionDuration: 8h\n116: \n117: ✓ **OpenAPI validation markers**\n118:   - All fields properly marked\n119:   - Validation constraints defined\n120: \n121: ✓ **Print columns for kubectl readability**\n122:   - Age column from creationTimestamp\n123: \n124: ✓ **JSON tag naming convention**\n125:   - All tags use camelCase\n126: \n127: ✓ **DeepCopy methods for safety**\n128:   - DeepCopy, DeepCopyInto, DeepCopyObject for all types\n129: \n130: ✓ **Validation markers for fields**\n131:   - kubebuilder validation markers applied\n132: \n133: ✓ **Label selector support**\n134:   - Standard Kubernetes label selectors\n135: \n136: ✓ **Watch support**\n137:   - Supported via client-go generated code\n138: \n139: ### Features Implemented\n140: \n141: #### Core Features\n142: - Complete CRD type definition with all required fields\n143: - Full OpenAPI v3 schema generation\n144: - Status subresource for independent status updates\n145: - Printer columns for kubectl\n146: - Default values for optional fields\n147: \n148: #### Sandbox Configuration\n149: - Complete pod template support\n150: - Container configuration (ports, env, resources, probes)\n151: - Volume support (emptyDir, configMap, secret, PVC)\n152: - Security context (runAsUser, capabilities, seccomp)\n153: - Scheduling (nodeSelector, affinity, tolerations)\n154: - Resource management (limits, requests)\n155: \n156: #### Integration\n157: - Scheme registration for serialization\n158: - DeepCopy methods for controller safety\n159: - Comprehensive test coverage\n160: - Documentation and examples\n161: \n162: ### Usage Example\n163: \n164: ```yaml\n165: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n166: kind: AgentRuntime\n167: metadata:\n168:   name: example-runtime\n169:   namespace: default\n170: spec:\n171:   podTemplate:\n172:     spec:\n173:       containers:\n174:       - name: agent\n175:         image: agent:latest\n176:         ports:\n177:         - containerPort: 8080\n178:   sessionTimeout: 15m\n179:   maxSessionDuration: 8h\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Testing\n183: \n184: Run the tests:\n185: ```bash\n186: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n187: ```\n188: \n189: All tests pass:\n190: ```\n191: PASS\n192: coverage: 0.9% of statements\n193: ok      github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1    0.007s\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### CRD Installation\n197: \n198: ```bash\n199: kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n200: kubectl get crd agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ### Client-go Integration\n204: \n205: The types are ready for client-go code generation:\n206: ```bash\n207: go run k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen \\\n208:   --input-base=. \\\n209:   --input=github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 \\\n210:   --output-package=github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go \\\n211:   --go-header-file=./hack/boilerplate.go.txt\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ## Conclusion\n215: \n216: The AR-001 implementation is complete with:\n217: - ✅ Full Go type definitions\n218: - ✅ Complete CRD YAML\n219: - ✅ Comprehensive test suite\n220: - ✅ Documentation and examples\n221: - ✅ All requirements from delta-spec satisfied\n222: - ✅ Ready for integration and use\n223: \n224: The implementation follows Kubernetes best practices and provides a solid foundation for the AgentCube sandbox orchestration platform.\n\n(End of file - total 224 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document summarizes the complete implementation of AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go | 732 | Complete Go type definitions for AgentRuntime CRD with all kubebuilder markers |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go | 48 | Scheme registration and API group configuration |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go | 12 | Package documentation and kubebuilder markers |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/deepcopy.go | 1086 | DeepCopy methods for all types |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go | 1029 | Comprehensive unit tests (32 test cases) |\n| pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md | 168 | Package documentation and usage examples |\n| config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml | 1028 | Complete CRD YAML definition with OpenAPI schema |\n| config/samples/runtime_v1alpha1_agentruntime.yaml | 99 | Example AgentRuntime YAML |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775896022101,"end":1775896022113}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896022117,"sessionID":"ses_28459852dffeE6AofOxt18H7zK","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba6cc45001KL8X5INsNPUI2g","messageID":"msg_d7ba6c00d001EcfW4aK3BVXPY1","sessionID":"ses_28459852dffeE6AofOxt18H7zK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1f09653ab215412c82de1afd53de22e2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `agentruntimes` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct with required fields: `PodTemplate` of type `*SandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout` of type `*metav1.Duration`, and `MaxSessionDuration` of type `*metav1.Duration`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires pod template\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `AgentRuntime` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `PodTemplate` must be non-nil and contains the sandbox pod template\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Duration fields use metav1 types\n33: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with timeouts configured\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` and `MaxSessionDuration` serialize as duration strings\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus with conditions support\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking runtime state transitions.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n42: - **GIVEN** a newly created `AgentRuntime` resource\n43: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n44: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n47: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `AgentRuntime` lifecycle\n48: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Creating → Running)\n49: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeList type for collection operations\n52: \n53: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]AgentRuntime` items and standard list metadata.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n56: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources in a namespace\n57: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n58: - **THEN** response returns an `AgentRuntimeList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n61: \n62: The system SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n65: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntime` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n66: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n67: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: List kind maps to AgentRuntimeList\n70: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntimeList`\n71: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n72: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntimeList` struct instance is created with items as `[]AgentRuntime`\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n75: \n76: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `AgentRuntime` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n79: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with both spec and status\n80: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n81: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n84: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n85: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n86: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `SessionTimeout` defaults to `\"15m\"` and `MaxSessionDuration` defaults to `\"8h\"`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing timeout fields receive defaults\n93: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created without explicit timeout values\n94: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n95: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` is set to `15m` and `MaxSessionDuration` to `8h` automatically\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n98: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created with custom timeout values\n99: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n100: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n103: \n104: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `AgentRuntime` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n107: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` without required `PodTemplate`\n108: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n109: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `podTemplate` is required\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Type validation for duration fields\n112: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` with invalid duration format\n113: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n114: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n117: \n118: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n121: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` resource that was created 5 minutes ago\n122: - **WHEN** `kubectl get agentruntimes` is executed\n123: - **THEN** the Age column shows `5m` or equivalent time duration\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n126: \n127: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n130: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `AgentRuntime` status every 30 seconds\n131: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n132: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL ensure `AgentRuntime` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n139: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n140: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create`\n141: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns an `AgentRuntime` pointer\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes AgentRuntime\n144: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n145: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called\n146: - **THEN** an informer watching `agentruntimes` resources is returned\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n149: \n150: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n153: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct populated with Go fields\n154: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n155: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`)\n156: \n157: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n158: \n159: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `AgentRuntime` to support safe copying in controllers.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n162: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` instance with populated fields\n163: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n164: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n167: \n168: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Duration fields validate format\n171: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `SessionTimeout` set to invalid duration\n172: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n173: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid duration format\n174: \n175: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n176: \n177: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `AgentRuntime` resources.\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n180: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources with different labels\n181: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n182: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n185: \n186: The system SHALL support watch operations on `AgentRuntime` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n189: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `AgentRuntime` resources\n190: - **WHEN** a new `AgentRuntime` is created\n191: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775896022104,"end":1775896022115}}}}
